FBIS4-63697 "drsov100_m_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-100 Daily Report 23 May 1994 Tajikistan Tajik Rebels Driven Back Across Afghan Border Tajik Rebels Driven Back Across Afghan Border LD2305133994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1104 GMT 23 May 94 LD2305133994 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Fighting broke out overnight between Russian border guards and Tajik rebels who tried to infiltrate into Tajikistan's Panj region from neighboring Afghanistan. There are no casualties among Russian troops, a military source told INTERFAX. No word is given of the number of killed or wounded on the rebels' side. There have been as many as four incidents since last Friday [20 May] in which Russian forces opened artillery and mortar fire on small groups of armed rebels as they tried to infiltrate the country along two sections of the Afghan border. None of Russian troops were hurt, but there is no word of casualties on the rebels' side. Any attempt at illegal border crossing will be suppressed, a senior official of the Russian Border Forces in Tajikistan said.
